					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12846781#post-4440541</guid>
				<title>Site Criticism Team - Staff Review</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12846781/and-then-it-was-morning#post-4440541</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 07 Dec 2019 17:37:51 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TheMightyMcB</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4483018</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is incredibly evocative of the feelings one goes through when losing a pet. Seeing them in pain, not being able to do anything about it, and just feeling helpless. All powerful emotions that you capitalized on by little things that Tubby does on his way out. Not eating, not playing, vomiting, being unable to climb into his favorite spot anymore, and lastly, banging his head into the wall. I'd imagine any person who has had to bury a pet has witnessed these heart wrenching sights of their loved ones in pain.</p> <p>If I had to point out one thing that I didn't like though, it would be that I found your opening incongruent with the rest of the piece. Discussing what might be wrong with Tubby only to jump back in time to when Bannock added Niles to the project felt a <em>little</em> jarring.</p> <p>Not enough to knock down my +1 though.</p> <p><span style="font-size:smaller;"><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> <em>Opinions expressed in this review do not reflect the opinions of SCP Wiki staff as a whole. Please respond to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/themightymcb" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4483018&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1575740271" alt="TheMightyMcB" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4483018)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/themightymcb" >TheMightyMcB</a></span> or contact the captain of the Site Criticism Team, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=637830&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1575740271" alt="SoullessSingularity" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=637830)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" >SoullessSingularity</a></span>, for any questions or concerns relating to this review.</em></span></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
