					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12846781#post-4440450</guid>
				<title>i&#039;m sorry little guy</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12846781/and-then-it-was-morning#post-4440450</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 07 Dec 2019 15:00:53 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>AbsentmindedNihilist</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2812984</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Thank you to everyone who critted this, including Naepic, CalibriBold, and several other people who I should have written down somewhere but didn't. If you looked at this and aren't mentioned here, let me know and I'll edit you in. Special mentions go to minathewitch for suggesting the title, and to Deadly_Bread for letting me use 4966 and Bannock.</p> <p>If you're here, you've probably finished the tale and are now probably supremely worried. Don't worry, I am too.</p> <p>This is a coping mechanism of sorts. It's an allegorical meditation on my own depression, and also my grandmother's dementia. It was written in one sitting and was originally not intended to be posted. The only reason I did was because for the first time in a long time, I was actually proud of the writing I'd done.</p> <p>Consider this my 3999.</p> <p>Thank you, and I'm sorry.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
